                <p>The Curvv is not just about safety—it also combines Tata Motors' next-gen design philosophy with a premium cabin, offering features such as an advanced infotainment system, connected car technology, and AI-driven enhancements. Positioned as a crossover SUV, the Tata Curvv will come in both ICE (internal combustion engine) and EV (electric vehicle) variants, catering to a wide audience in India.</p>
                <p>The success of the Tata Curvv further establishes Tata Motors as a frontrunner in the Indian automotive industry, especially in the growing segment of electric mobility. With its top-notch safety features and innovative design, the Curvv is expected to make a strong impact when it hits the market.</p>
